Articles.Content:
Is it normal to have a yellow warning in debugging "high Logic" when switching from space center to menu... or flight, or VAB,.... ?

The game works fine, stock, with this warning but Im trying to get a huge modpack to run in x64. Im wondering if this warning could cause me problems when I add new mods? I know x64 has problems but, the mods I have working great together are using about 8.5Gb and when finished its going to be around 10Gb in use (with ATM compression so i have to run this x64). I am very close to having all the mods im wanting to work, working, with this "high logic" warning but, since I have the warning on a stock freshly installed Steam version KSP, I thought I should ask.

Thanks for such a GREAT GAME YALL lol
Yep. Totally normal. Don't worry about it.
As a general rule, things labelled 'warning' and in yellow can be safely ignored. Worry more about things labelled 'exception' and highlighted in red.

Worry more about things labelled 'exception' and highlighted in red.

I am glad you made this point, thank you. When you have an Exception, is it from what ever is logged in the previous line in debugging?
